Summer revenue is already pacing 12 percent behind last year and could end up down 15 percent, one of the worst declines in modern history.

Call it the August Death March at the domestic box office.

Over the Aug. 11-13 weekend, revenue plunged 32 percent behind the same frame last year sans a successful August tentpole such as Suicide Squad (2016) or Guardians of the Galaxy (2014), furthering a steady erosion in ticket sales that has gripped the summer box office almost every weekend since War for the Planet of the Apes launched in the
